name: Choosing Symbol Pairs
description:
There is a given string S consisting of N symbols. Your task is to find the
number of ordered pairs of integers i and j such that 11̇ ≤ i, j ≤ N 2Ṡ[i] = S[j], that is the i-th symbol of string S is equal to the j-th. Input
The single input line contains S, consisting of lowercase Latin letters and
digits. It is guaranteed that string S in not empty and its length does not
exceed 10^5. Output Print a single number which represents the number of pairs
i and j with the needed property. Pairs (x, y) and (y, x) should be considered
different, i.e. the ordered pairs count. Examples Input great10 Output 7 Input
aaaaaaaaaa Output 100
